Two dimensional HashMap.

The two dimensional hash map is implemented as a hash map of hash maps. Each "row" key points to a "column" hash map.

Example of use:

Map2D map = new HashMap2D(); map.put( "a" , "b" , "my value" ); String s = map.get( "a" , "b" );

Note: HashMap2D does not implement the Map interface.
